### 8. Test Coverage Scope

**Priority 1: Must Have (Core Operations)**
- Health check (`healthCheck()`)
- Index CRUD (`createIndex()`, `deleteIndex()`, index exists check)
- Bulk indexing with real documents (`bulkIndex()`)
- Basic search without neural (`search()` with match/bool queries)
- Error handling (connection failures, invalid data)

**Priority 2: Should Have (Advanced Operations)**
- ML Commons API (model group search - without registration)
- Pipeline creation (ingest + search pipelines)
- Pipeline deletion
- Data transformation logic (style Ôćĺ OpenSearch document)

**Priority 3: Nice to Have (Manual/Skipped)**
- Full bootstrap flow (model deployment)
- Neural search with embeddings
- Model deployment + task polling

**Estimated Test Count**: 
- OpensearchService: 15-20 tests
- OpensearchNeuralService: 10-15 tests (non-neural operations only)
- **Total**: 25-35 tests, ~3-5 minutes execution time

