## Trade-offs & Decisions Summary

| Decision | Rationale | Trade-off |
|----------|-----------|-----------|
| Skip ML model deployment in tests | Keep tests fast (<5 min) | Neural search not tested in CI (acceptable - can test manually) |
| Dynamic index naming | Prevent conflicts, enable parallel tests (future) | Slightly more complex cleanup |
| Single OpenSearch container | Simplicity, resource efficiency | No cluster testing (not needed) |
| Port 9200 (standard) | Consistency with OpenSearch defaults | Requires local docker-compose update |
| Two-tier test approach | Fast regular tests + optional slow tests | Neural search testing requires manual execution |
| Real OpenSearch in tests | Tests actual integrations, catches real issues | Slightly slower than mocks (acceptable) |

